#compdef gormt
# =============================================================================
# gormt — xxjwxc's "database to golang struct" — a Go
#         CLI that connects to a MySQL / PostgreSQL /
#         SQLite database, reflects all tables in the
#         specified schema, and emits Go struct
#         definitions with GORM tag annotations,
#         JSON/URL serialization tags, and optional
#         foreign-key relationship struct fields.
#         Designed as the "scaffold the boring part"
#         tool for Go developers building APIs on top
#         of existing legacy databases — gormt produces
#         the entire data-access layer (struct
#         definitions + GORM ORM tags + optional
#         CRUD functions) from the live database
#         schema in seconds, instead of hand-coding
#         each struct.  Used heavily in Chinese Go
#         enterprise development (xxjwxc is a Chinese
#         developer; primary documentation in
#         Simplified Chinese with English translations).
#         Distinguishing from sqlc (SQL → typesafe Go;
#         in our corpus), ent (Facebook entity framework;
#         in our corpus), gorm-gen (jinzhu/gen; same
#         purpose, less popular), xo/xo (Brian Snyder's
#         schema → Go struct generator), gnomock (mocked
#         databases for tests), Atlas (declarative
#         migration), and goose (migration runner) by:
#           - GORM ORM TARGET — emits structs with
#             gorm.io/gorm-compatible struct tags
#             (`gorm:"primaryKey;column:id"`, `gorm:
#             "type:varchar(255);not null"`, etc.)
#             ready to drop into a GORM-based codebase
#             (this is the headline CLI library that
#             closes Axis 35 on the Go side; see
#             taxonomy notes below)
#           - REFLECTION-FROM-RUNNING-DB — connects via
#             standard MySQL driver, executes SHOW
#             TABLES / DESCRIBE / SHOW CREATE TABLE /
#             SHOW INDEX FROM queries, and reflects
#             every column type + nullability +
#             default + auto-increment + index +
#             foreign-key relationship
#           - GUI + CLI MODES — `-g, --gui` enables a
#             terminal-UI mode (using jroimartin/gocui)
#             for interactive table-selection +
#             column-mapping; default is non-GUI
#             scripted mode
#           - FOREIGN-KEY STRUCT INCLUSION — `-f,
#             --foreign` includes foreign-key relations
#             as embedded struct fields with appropriate
#             GORM relation tags (`gorm:"foreignKey:..."`)
#           - URL TAG EMISSION — `-l, --url` adds tags
#             for JSON / URL marshaling alongside GORM
#             tags; useful for web API handlers that
#             need both DB binding + HTTP request
#             marshaling on the same struct
#           - FUNCTION EXPORT — `-F, --fun` emits CRUD
#             function stubs (CreateXXX, GetXXX,
#             UpdateXXX, DeleteXXX) alongside the
#             struct definitions
#           - SINGULAR / PLURAL CONTROL — `-s,
#             --singular` (default true) keeps table
#             names singular in Go (e.g., "User" not
#             "Users") to match GORM's convention
#           - TABLE PREFIX — `-t, --table_prefix STR`
#             strips a common prefix from table names
#             before generating struct names (e.g.,
#             `t_users` → `User` with `-t t_`)
#           - SELECTIVE TABLE PROCESSING — `-b,
#             --table_names "users,orders,products"`
#             generates structs for only the specified
#             tables; default is all tables in the
#             schema
#           - COBRA + VALIDATOR.V9 — uses spf13/cobra
#             (Axis 1 argparse covered) + go-playground/
#             validator.v9 for required-flag enforcement
#           - I18N SUPPORT — uses nicksnyder/go-i18n/v2
#             for localized error messages + UI strings
#             (Chinese + English supported)
#           - YAML CONFIG ALTERNATIVE — `sql.yml` +
#             `config.yml` in the working directory can
#             override CLI flags; useful for
#             repeated-invocation projects
#         Used by: Chinese Go enterprises rapidly
#         scaffolding API layers on top of legacy MySQL
#         schemas, freelance Go developers consulting
#         on Chinese projects (gormt is the de-facto
#         Chinese-language Go ORM scaffold), data-
#         migration teams porting legacy database
#         schemas to GORM-based Go services, and
#         instructors teaching Go database integration.
#
# Author:  xxjwxc on GitHub.  Chinese Go developer.
